              <td class="py-3 font-mono text-sm">$$</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink"><a href="/conveyor-types/spiral-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">Spiral</a></td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Elevation changes</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">50-200 FPM</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">Up to 75 lbs</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">No</td>
              <td class="py-3 font-mono text-sm">$$$$</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink"><a href="/conveyor-types/vertical-reciprocating/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">VRC</a></td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Mezzanine transport</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">20-40 FPM</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">Up to 6,000 lbs</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">No</td>
              <td class="py-3 font-mono text-sm">$$$-$$$$</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink"><a href="/conveyor-types/tabletop-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">Tabletop Chain</a></td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Bottles, cans, cartons</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">20-100 FPM</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">Up to 50 lbs</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Limited</td>
              <td class="py-3 font-mono text-sm">$$</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-4">Relative cost: $ = lowest, $$$$ = highest. Actual pricing depends on length, materials, controls, and manufacturer. See the <a href="/resources/conveyor-cost-guide/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">conveyor cost guide</a> for detailed pricing factors.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Category Breakdown -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim bg-dots" aria-labelledby="categories-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Category Breakdown</div>
      <h2 id="categories-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Conveyor Types by <span class="text-accent">Category</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-8">

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink mb-3">Roller Conveyors</h3>
          <p><a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Roller conveyors</a> represent the largest conveyor category in packaging. They use cylindrical rollers mounted in side frames to transport flat-bottomed products. The four primary sub-types are <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/gravity/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">gravity roller</a> (unpowered), <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/powered/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">powered roller</a> (belt-driven or line-shaft), <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR</a> (motor driven roller), and <a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">CDLR</a> (chain driven live roller). Manufacturers like Hytrol, Interroll, and Dematic produce roller conveyor systems for case weights from 5 lbs to over 10,000 lbs.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink mb-3">Belt Conveyors</h3>
          <p>Belt conveyors use a continuous belt surface to transport products. They handle irregular shapes, soft-bottom bags, loose items, and incline/decline applications that roller conveyors cannot. Flat belt, cleated belt, and modular plastic belt are the three main sub-types. Dorner, mk North America, and Hytrol are major <a href="/conveyor-types/belt-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">belt conveyor manufacturers</a> for packaging applications.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink mb-3">Accumulation Conveyors</h3>
          <p><a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Accumulation conveyors</a> buffer product between upstream and downstream processes. They absorb line stops, speed mismatches, and operator breaks without shutting down the entire <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">packaging line</a>. Zero-pressure accumulation (ZPA) and minimum-pressure accumulation are the two primary modes. <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR technology</a> dominates new ZPA installations.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink mb-3">Transfer &#x26; Sortation Conveyors</h3>
          <p><a href="/conveyor-types/transfer-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Transfer conveyors</a> change product direction at right angles or multiple angles. Pop-up transfers, turntables, push diverters, and right-angle chain transfers handle different speed and load requirements. <a href="/conveyor-types/diverting-merging/sortation/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Sortation systems</a> extend this concept to high-speed multi-lane routing for distribution and fulfillment applications.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink mb-3">Vertical Conveyors</h3>
          <p><a href="/conveyor-types/vertical-reciprocating/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Vertical reciprocating conveyors (VRCs)</a> lift product between floor levels or mezzanines. They provide an alternative to freight elevators with simpler code requirements and lower installation cost. Spiral conveyors provide continuous vertical transport without the stop-and-go cycle of reciprocating units.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink mb-3">Specialty Conveyors</h3>
          <p>Specialty conveyor types address specific packaging needs. <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/beverage/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Tabletop chain conveyors</a> handle bottles and cans on high-speed <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">food and beverage lines</a>. Vibratory conveyors feed bulk parts and powders. <a href="/conveyor-types/magnetic-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Magnetic conveyors</a> transport ferrous lids and cans. <a href="/conveyor-types/vacuum-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Vacuum conveyors</a> grip thin films, labels, and pouches that standard belts cannot hold.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Industry Applications -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="applications-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Applications</div>
      <h2 id="applications-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Conveyor Types by <span class="text-accent">Industry</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p><a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Food and beverage packaging lines</a> typically use <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/sanitary/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">sanitary stainless steel belt conveyors</a>, tabletop chain conveyors for bottles, and <a href="/conveyor-types/washdown-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">washdown-rated roller conveyors</a> for cased goods. USDA and 3-A sanitary standards drive material and design requirements.</p>
        <p><a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">General packaging lines</a> combine multiple conveyor types. A typical end-of-line system includes belt conveyors feeding a case packer, <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/powered/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">powered roller conveyors</a> transporting sealed cases, <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">accumulation conveyors</a> buffering before a palletizer, and <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/pallet/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">pallet conveyors</a> moving loaded pallets to stretch wrap and shipping.</p>
        <p>Distribution and fulfillment centers rely on <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR conveyors</a> for zone-controlled accumulation, sortation systems for multi-lane routing, and <a href="/conveyor-types/vertical-reciprocating/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">VRCs</a> for mezzanine transport. <a href="/resources/automated-conveyor-systems/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Automated conveyor systems</a> integrate these types with warehouse management software (WMS) for hands-free product flow.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How many types of conveyors are there?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>The packaging industry uses over 30 distinct conveyor types. Major categories include <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">roller conveyors</a> (gravity, powered, MDR, CDLR), belt conveyors (flat, cleated, modular), chain conveyors (tabletop, drag, slat), <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">accumulation conveyors</a>, <a href="/conveyor-types/transfer-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">transfer conveyors</a>, spiral conveyors, sortation systems, and <a href="/conveyor-types/vertical-reciprocating/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">vertical reciprocating conveyors</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is the most common conveyor type in packaging?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Belt conveyors and <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">roller conveyors</a> are the two most common types. Belt conveyors handle lightweight and irregular products. Roller conveyors dominate case and carton transport. <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR roller conveyors</a> have become the standard for zone-controlled accumulation in distribution centers.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How do I choose the right conveyor type?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Conveyor selection depends on five key factors: product characteristics (weight, size, shape, bottom surface), throughput requirement (units per minute), function needed (transport, accumulate, sort, elevate), environment (food-grade, washdown, cleanroom), and budget. Define these requirements first, then match them against conveyor type capabilities using the comparison table above.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is the difference between a belt conveyor and a roller conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Belt conveyors use a continuous belt surface and carry products of any shape or bottom condition. <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Roller conveyors</a> use cylindrical rollers and require flat, rigid bottoms spanning at least 3 rollers. Belt conveyors handle inclines and declines. Roller conveyors offer easier zone control, <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">accumulation</a>, and lower friction for heavy loads.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What conveyor types support zero-pressure accumulation?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Three conveyor types commonly provide zero-pressure accumulation (ZPA). <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR conveyors</a> use independent 24VDC motorized zones. <a href="/conveyor-types/live-roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Belt-driven live roller conveyors</a> use pneumatic clutches or band brakes per zone. <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Dedicated accumulation conveyors</a> with photo-eye sensors and zone controllers manage product spacing. MDR dominates new ZPA installations.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

